[thinking] **Considering container conflicts**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about a situation where a new container starts with the same name or port (5433) that an existing class is using. It seems that JUnit might run tests sequentially, which could lead to conflicts if parallel execution is disabled. If that’s the case, both test classes attempting to use the same port/container name could cause issues. To avoid this, I should create unique containers/ports, maybe using 5434. This seems like a solid plan!
[thinking] 
