[assistant] Adjusted the PostgreSQL-based array-param tests to avoid connecting to PostgreSQL during bootstrap.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Fixes made:
[assistant] - Rewrote:
[assistant]   - `ReactiveMultiIdEntityLoaderArrayParamTest.java`
[assistant]   - `ReactiveEntityBatchLoaderArrayParamTest.java`
[assistant] - The tests now:
[assistant]   - Build the Hibernate Reactive `EntityManagerFactory` with an explicit `PostgreSQLDialect`.
[assistant]   - Disable JDBC metadata access:
[assistant]     - `hibernate.boot.allow_jdbc_metadata_access=false`
[assistant]     - `hibernate.temp.use_jdbc_metadata_defaults=false`
[assistant]   - Do **not** start Docker PostgreSQL.
[assistant]   - Do **not** open a reactive session or execute a PostgreSQL query.
[assistant]   - Still reach the relevant array loader `prepare()` path, including the active `ReactiveMultiIdEntityLoaderArrayParam.createTypedArray(...)` dynamic-access call site.
[assistant] - Updated `persistence.xml` for the PostgreSQL array-param persistence unit with the same no-metadata-access settings.
[assistant] - Removed the unnecessary explicit SCRAM dependency and PostgreSQL Docker image usage; kept `vertx-pg-client` because the PostgreSQL URL still requires the PostgreSQL Vert.x driver at bootstrap.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Why this fixes the failure:
[assistant] - The failure came from `io.vertx.pgclient.impl.codec.DataTypeCodec` parsing PostgreSQL BC date metadata on JDK 25 while Hibernate tried to inspect the database.
[assistant] - The tests only need PostgreSQL dialect SQL-array support, not a live PostgreSQL connection.
[assistant] - Disabling JDBC metadata access avoids the Vert.x PostgreSQL query path entirely.
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run the Gradle test command locally, per instruction.
[assistant-event] text_end
