ostgreSQL array-param persistence unit with the same no-metadata-access settings.\n- Removed the unnecessary explicit SCRAM dependency and PostgreSQL Docker image usage; kept `vertx-pg-client` because the PostgreSQL URL still requires the PostgreSQL Vert.x driver at bootstrap.\n\nWhy this fixes the failure:\n- The failure came from `io.vertx.pgclient.impl.codec.DataTypeCodec` parsing PostgreSQL BC date metadata on JDK 25 while Hibernate tried to inspect the database.\n- The tests only need PostgreSQL dialect SQL-array support, not a live PostgreSQL connection.\n- Disabling JDBC metadata access avoids the Vert.x PostgreSQL query path entirely.\n\nI did not run the Gradle test command locally, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e678c877676a4ab016a15e7b126f0819ea6b8d7e8c6dcbaf4\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 642, "output": 635, "cacheRead": 73728, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 75005, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779820457053, "responseId": "resp_0e678c877676a4ab016a15e7aa55f8819eb956cfa056a3e99b"}, "toolResults": []}
